WHAT WE ARE LOOKING FOR 
About the Team 
Based at the Military Vehicle Centre of Excellence site located in Redbank, QLD, you will be a key member of the Electronic Solutions Software team and work in partnership with Technical/Project Managers and project teams on the design, construction, monitoring and maintenance of the secure CI/CD pipeline and associated tools for the Training Equipment teams.
 About the Role
 You will be responsible for the design, construction, monitoring and maintenance of the secure CI/CD pipeline and associated tools for the Training Equipment teams.

     As DevOps Engineer, you can anticipate some of your day-to-day tasks to include:


Collaborate with Managers, Software Leads and Developers to understand software development needs and requirements;
Design and build production quality, secure CI/CD pipeline;
Ensure the compliance of the development environment with the defence security requirements;
Plan & implement Continuous Deployment concepts for the Training Equipment such as simulators;
Accountable for software development continuity, efficiency and security;
Author support documents including plans, requirements, design documentation, operating procedures and status reports; and
Provide technical guidance on development operations, managing code deployments and fixes & updates.





WHAT QUALIFICATIONS YOU SHOULD HAVE 
What are we looking for?
 Rheinmetall seeks applicants who exemplify our Company’s values of Safety, Partnering, Openness, Respect and Trust. This creates a workplace environment where employees value each other, live up to their promises and communicate openly.
 The experience and skillset best suited to this role includes:

Proven experience in a DevOps Engineer role;
A high level of proficiency in applying DevOps practices and techniques to Linux & Windows based software development environments;
Practical experience in applying popular CI/CD (i.e. Gitlab CI/CD)tools;
Administration experience with software collaboration tools such as GitLab, Jira, and Confluence;
Experience in building mixed Windows and Linux development environments;
Experience applying security risk management processes to software development systems;
Experience administering and using Docker, Artifactory and Conan;
Experience working in defence programs would be desirable;
Tertiary qualifications in IT, Software Engineering, Computer Science or related field;
Ability to travel internationally and interstate, when required; and
Must hold or be eligible to obtain an Australian Government Security Clearance (must hold Australian Citizenship).

At Rheinmetall, your strengths and experience are worth something. We also highly value diversity and equal opportunity. We look forward to receiving your application. 




WHAT WE OFFER YOU 

Have a long weekend every second week with a 9 day working fortnight
Working in a great team and with exciting products
State of the art facilities with onsite subsidized cafeteria
Internal incentive and referral program
Opportunity for career development and further training
Strong links to our global Rheinmetall community
Opportunity to work on major projects such as LAND 400
Attractive Remuneration package with salary sacrificing & novated leases
Flexibility in workplace settings offering opportunities to work in multiple locations
Corporate discounts with gyms, private health funds and various car dealerships
Employee Assistance Program to support our employees and their families overall wellbeing





WHO WE ARE 
Rheinmetall Defence Australia (RDA) is a major Defence company with operations across Australia and New Zealand delivering specialist Defence capability to the Australian Defence Force and New Zealand Defence Force. RDA is a subsidiary of Rheinmetall, a global technology group based in Dusseldorf, Germany. RDA is a trusted partner to the ADF through its three divisions - Vehicle Systems, Electronics Solutions and Weapon and Ammunition. RDA is rapidly growing its Australian footprint to deliver system solutions and capabilty to the ADF in the areas of mobility, lethality, reconnaissance, protection and sustainment.
 Rheinmetall recognises the strength that comes with employee diversity. We are commited to providing an inclusive work environment where each employee is treated fairly and respectfully. Diversity is critical to our ability to work sucessfully as a team regardless of borders, language or culture. Our workforce includes employees of varying gender, age, race and ethnicity, professional and cultural background.
 Veterans are always encouraged to apply for roles at Rheinmetall where they can bring select skills and expertise to the delivery of products and services for our customer. Recognising these unique attributes, the Company has established a Veterans Employment Program that trains and supports veterans transitioning from the armed forces and seeking future employment in the commercial sector.

     As an integrated technology group with more than 25,000 employees worldwide, the listed Rheinmetall AG stands for a strong, internationally successful company that operates in various markets with an innovative range of products and services. As a renowned development partner and direct supplier to the global automotive industry and a leading international systems provider for security technology, Rheinmetall draws on its high level of expertise in its basic technologies to address long-term megatrends, identify viable new markets with high growth potential and develop innovative solutions for a safe and liveable future. The focus on sustainability is an integral part of Rheinmetall's strategy. The company aims to achieve CO2 neutrality by 2035.

Company Description
 Every person at Leidos plays an important and valued role bringing science, engineering and technology together to produce practical solutions for our customers’ most complex problems. It’s how we help to make the world safer, healthier and more efficient - work that matters and a mission, like those of our customers, we are passionate about. We’re open minded, ambitious and committed to enabling our people to do their best work, to be inspired by what they can achieve and the impact they can have.
Here in Australia, we’re agile and growing fast. Our 1,400 employees are busy building an enviable reputation for innovation and delivery. And, as part of a US-based organisation with 37,000 people and a 50 year history, we are able to draw upon world-leading technical expertise to help us provide the best solutions to our customers.



Job Description
 Your New Role
We have multiple opportunities available for Software Engineers to join our high performing Command, Control, Communications & Computers, Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance (C4ISR) line of business, working on an exciting, nationally significant, and highly visible federal government customer. The project is focussed on developing the data processing platform that drives one of the most visited websites in Australia. The roles are multi-faceted as we are looking for unique individuals whom are able to contribute broadly across the software development lifecycle in a range of ways, including but not limited to: agile software development; DevOps; Data Integration; Release Management; Software Management; Sustainment; and Database administration.
The individuals we are looking for are highly motivated software engineers and able to work flexibly as either a domain specialist, focussed on expertise within a narrow field of view, or with broad experience across the lifecycle, and interested in managing teams and leading people.
The individuals we are looking for will also be experience in and appreciate the ins and outs of system development methodologies, tools, practices and approaches such that best practices and novel concepts can be thoughtfully devised and experimented with in our endless search for optimal development and delivery performance.
The successful candidate(s) will have strong analytical and troubleshooting skills, experience in integrating multi-technology platforms, solid communication skills and a desire to tackle complex problems in a unique environment. We are looking for hands-on and experienced people that love everything about building software, solving engineering problems, and leveraging innovative ideas and technologies.



Qualifications
 About You and What You'll Bring
Attributes, attitudes and behaviours that will be highly desirable include and of the following:

A love of all things software and a desire to solve interesting problems through coding;
Being adaptable to change and pivoting where required;
Significant hands-on experience in delivering a variety of software solutions;
Experience in the design and implementation of DevSecOps approaches to software development;
Being familiar with a range of relevant technologies including but not limited to: Java, NiFi, Ansible, Spring, Python, PostgreSQL;
Being familiar with a range of relevant technical domains including but not limited to: geospatial technologies; data management; automated build and deployments; cloud technologies;
Hand-on experience in setting up software development tool-chains including but not limited to configuration management tools, artefact management tools, code quality and security analysis tools, automated testing tools, integrated software development environments, continuous integration tools, collaboration tools, and software and architecture modelling tools.
Understand and uses appropriate modelling approaches, including logical models of components, modules and interfaces, to contribute to the development of systems and software architectures in specific business or functional areas;
Provides advice on technical aspects of system development and integration (including requests for changes, deviations from specifications, etc.) and ensures that relevant technical strategies, policies, standards and practices (including security) are applied correctly;
A hands-on preference to approaching your work with a strong desire to solve problems by doing;
A strong level of familiarity with software development lifecycles and related best practices such as those related to human engineering, user experience engineering, software safety, and others;
Real end-to-end experience with the delivery of an software development program from cradle to grave;
Strong levels of comfort in managing ambiguity and making decisions even where information is incomplete or unclear;
A Strong desire to tackle and solve problems, including problems that are challenging and complex;
A love of immersion in a field or discipline of interest that enables deep operational and business insights to be learned and superior conclusions to be drawn;
A lack of satisfaction if you see a process or procedure or methodology that is sub-optimal, that you have not improved, enhanced or in some way made better;
A curiosity for novel and new ideas and problems that you are then able to use your experience and knowledge to help solve;
Either or both of: a keen attention to detail or an ability to understand the big picture in the context of problem solving, analysis and design;
Comfort in working as an individual contributor and as a part of a team depending on the task at hand;
Experience within an agile development team will be very useful including SCRUM or Kanban;
Excellent English written and verbal communication skills;
Solid organizational skills including the ability manage staff that may or may-not being directly reporting to you;
Highly effective in managing multiple, concurrent activities, while understanding and managing priorities, dependencies and risk; and
A natural leader in your own way of providing the leadership that ensures your ability to influence others in a positive way to achieve important outcomes.

Additional Information
 This role does require the successful applicant to be an Australian Citizen and to be able to hold an NV-1 security clearance.
What you’ll love
At Leidos you’ll enjoy 12 weeks’ paid parental leave as a primary carer, flexible work practices, discounted health insurance, novated leasing and more. Foster your career through complete access to learning and development and mentoring opportunities, we have a strong track record of internal promotion and career transitions. Join a company who acknowledges “People First”.

Hudson have partnered with a global consultancy working closely with one of Australia's largest financial institutions. This is an opportunity for a DevOps engineer with cloud migration experience to secure a 12 month initial contract working on collaborative, large-scale projects.
 Working fully remotely based in Australia, you will enjoy great flexibility working within an Australian household name.
 The ideal candidate will have:

Experience with large-scale cloud migration projects;
Demonstrated experience designing and implementing CI/CD pipelines using Jenkins;
Infrastructure as Code experience using Terraform or AWS CloudFormation;
Proficiency in either AWS or Azure Cloud platforms.

